<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910522-0023</DOCNO><DOCID>910522-0023.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Raytheon Co.:   British Aerospace Is Partner   In Pursuing U.K. Contract</HL><DATE>05/22/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A16</SO><CO>   RTN U.BA</CO><MS>TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>AEROSPACE (ARO)DIVERSIFIED TECHNOLOGY (DTC)</IN><RE>MASSACHUSETTS (MA)GREAT BRITAIN (UK)</RE><LP>   Raytheon Co., Lexington, Mass., said it signed anagreement with British Aerospace Ltd. to jointly compete fora contract with the United Kingdom's Ministry of Defense,using Patriot missiles as the star attraction.   The Ministry, according to Raytheon, will soon requestbids to replace its current medium-range surface-to-airmissile system, the Bloodhound.</LP><TEXT>   The two companies said they plan to offer a comprehensiveair-defense system in which the Patriot -- known for its roleagainst Iraqi Scud missiles during the Persian Gulf war --will operate with British Aerospace's missile, Rapier 2000.   Raytheon, a defense concern, said it will be the primecontractor under the agreement, while British Aerospace willcoordinate subcontractors in Britain.   Raytheon said there are six to 12 other companiesworld-wide competing for the contract.</TEXT></DOC>